Product_Key.Name: Microsoft Dynamics NAV
Product_Key.Key:
<p><b>Microsoft Dynamics® NAV 4.0 and 5.0</b></p>
<p>To install Microsoft® Business Solutions-Navision®, now part of Microsoft Dynamics®, select Demo on the CD menu and then Install Demonstration Version. When you get to the screen where you can select the type of installation, you must select Complete. This installs the complete version of Microsoft Dynamics NAV, with the complete application. It is the license file that determines what you have access to.</p>
<p>The MSDN license file is required to unlock additional functionality in Microsoft Dynamics NAV. To complete your Microsoft Dynamics NAV installation, you must download and import the MSDN license file. To do this, from the Microsoft Dynamics NAV application screen, click Tools, License Information, and then click Import. After importing the MSDN license file, close the license information window and then click File and select the Cronus company to open the application again.</p>
<p>The MSDN license file gives access to Microsoft Dynamics NAV functionality, with the following restrictions:</p><ul> 
<li>You can only enter dates in November, December, January, and February.</li>
<li>The size of the database can be a maximum of 100MB.</li>
<li>You are only allowed to make 4000 write transactions in a database.</li></ul>
<p>In addition, you can modify the following objects in the Object Designer:</p><ul> 
<li>Table 18 can be modified. Fields from 99,990 through 99,999 can be inserted.</li> 
<li>Forms 21 and 22 can be modified. Forms 99,998 and 99,999 can be inserted.</li> 
<li>Report 101 can be modified. Report 99,999 can be inserted.</li>
<li>MenuSuite 90 can be inserted.</li>
<li>XML Port 99,999 can be inserted.</li></ul>
<p>With the MSDN license, you can create new objects (tables, forms, reports, and so on) in the object range from 123,456,700 through 123,456,799. It is not possible to edit the standard Microsoft Dynamics NAV objects or the objects dedicated to customer solutions.</p>
<p>You can learn about how to develop in Microsoft Dynamics NAV by reading the Application Designer&#39;s Guide. To access the Application Designer&#39;s Guide on CD 1, click Tools on the main menu.</p>
<p>To get access to a Microsoft Dynamics NAV Developer License file, with access to the Microsoft Dynamics NAV application source code, you will need to become a Microsoft Partner. Please see the <a href="https://mspartner.microsoft.com/en/us/Pages/Solutions/microsoft-dynamics.aspx">Microsoft Partner Network</a> for more information.</p>
